[32m+[m[32mA fully automated Python pipeline for building, running, and post-processing a[m
[32m+[m[32m**coupled thermo-hydraulic (TH) geothermal doublet simulation** in FEFLOW 8.1.[m
 The pipeline takes a single Excel workbook as input and produces a completed[m
[31m-simulation plus publication-quality figures without any manual GUI interaction.[m
[32m+[m[32m100-year simulation and seven publication-quality diagnostic figures without any[m
[32m+[m[32mmanual interaction with the FEFLOW GUI.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe core technical contribution is a **`singleStep()` workaround** for a[m
[32m+[m[32mverified regression in the FEFLOW 8.1 IFM Python API that prevents enumeration[m
[32m+[m[32mof multi-snapshot DAC result files — enabling reliable access to all simulation[m
[32m+[m[32msnapshots through a parallel NumPy archive.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Context:** This pipeline was developed for the MSc course *Geothermal Energy[m
[32m+[m[32m> Systems* at Politecnico di Torino, following the methodology of the FEFLOW[m
[32m+[m[32m> Geothermal Energy Tutorial (Casasso, rev00, 03/06/2024). The numerical[m
[32m+[m[32m> experiment simulates 100 years of doublet operation in a sedimentary reservoir[m
[32m+[m[32m> at 870–1120 m depth.[m
[32m+[m
